  "text": "An automated Rotorod (Ugo Basile) was used to assess vestibulomotor function. [CITATION_1] On the day before hemorrhage induction, mice underwent 2 consecutive conditioning trials at a set rotational speed (16 revolutions/min) for 60 sec followed by 3 additional trials with an accelerating rotational speed. The average time to fall from the rotating cylinder in the latter 3 trials was recorded as baseline latency. After injury, mice underwent consecutive daily testing with 3 trials of accelerating rotational speed (intertrial interval of 15 min). Average latency to fall from the rod was recorded. Mice unable to grasp the rotating rod were given a latency of 0 sec.",
